            <c id="aspace_84b5562189b505146e27ca8dda292c42" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Correspondence concerning calcium carbide in operations for cancer of the cervix</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1898-1899</unitdate>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_066cac2dca9f4b857bfcb942b2832cbc">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>In the issue of July 2, 1898, Etheridge had published an article, A Note on the Treatmenr of Carcinoma of the Uterus," in which he asked for information from others on treatment by calcium carbide. These letters were grouped by Etheridge.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="aspace_9f9fd83885bb580fd1930c3c2cc34dc2" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Correspondence: "Military"</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1894-1896</unitdate>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_e4e7a2d7bd4044bf307dedd9e08b3a5e">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>These materials were groued by Etheridge. He had served in the Civil War and had later served in the First Brigade, Illinis National Guard.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
