            <c id="aspace_5dc78eedec7246da86e0a4eb3d394288" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Case histories</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1869-1879</unitdate>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_6ad354a1c6559e772e6b079e4cbb4155">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>In this bound volume (33x21 cm), Eheridge wrote a full account of his cases and treatment. The volume begins with a few pages on notes on a course of anatomy and physiology he attended in Ann Arbor, Michigan, in 1866. Some docuemnts are inserted in the volume, including a letter and case history of Mrs. Hubbard sent by Dr. E. L. Homes, March 10, 1880</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="aspace_a93f65ba85720052dc650f0901719f35" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Patient ledger</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1869-1871</unitdate>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_514c550ec183b24260f41905916df4aa">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Bound volume (31x14 cm) lists patients by day, chargesaand payments. There is an index to names at the beginning of the volume. The book had little information on diagnoses and treatments.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="aspace_9d50cff00208c3148bd957633b2d6e1c" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Account of travel to London</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1970 November-1870 December</unitdate>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_b63a4fd11c249de98cd4d0ac3242de24">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Bound volume (24x20 cm) with an account of his experiences in London. Etheridge married in 1870. He noted that they had spent the months of September through the most of November visiting Paris, Switzerland, Italy, Austria, Bavaria, Wurtemberg, Saxony, Russia, the Rhine and Belgium, and had now (November 26) arrived in London. "Our chief on\bject here is to benefit me, by walking the hospitalas &amp; gaining all the information I can here elicit, professionally. The chief object of this book is [to] note down things aaf interest..."  Most of the remainde4r of thebook lists menus and recipes.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="aspace_5ba35a39e9d70692bbfccace44824912" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>St. Vincent Hall prescriptions</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1871-1872</unitdate>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_827510d8c4ba540de57dc4bb3f799c64">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Possibly St. Vincent Hall was a dispensary. The bound volume in pencil (20x16 cm) gives the date, the name of the patient, and the prescripion.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="aspace_4b2fd6edbdc14f34ab4bc7cb3575a44a" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Patient ledger</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1887-1891</unitdate>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_2e4864c1213beea76030f745989e66cd">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Large bound volume (37x23cm) containing an index of names, and a list of patients, dates of visits, amounts billed, and amounts paid.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="aspace_907bcf729627e05ae9529bf4441abcc7" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Cash book  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1891 June-1899 February</unitdate>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_caa6f65e269f8cb86db3bec5fae81024">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>This bound volume (22x14 cm.) stamped "Cash" in goldleaf on the front cover, has been organized by month. For each month, Etheridge listed several entries for "Office" followed by the names of various people, and amounts of money.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="aspace_9bb7219673098b6182c51097e1e698ad" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Record of patients and operations</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1893 October-1894 December</unitdate>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_daea86cecb769a83152863f9725e2ad4">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Bound pre-printed volume (23x15 cm.) with "Dr. Etheridge" in gold leaf on the cover. There is no indication if there was a publisher. The open pages have columns for date, name of patient, name of [refering] physician, fees, operation, arrival, and remarks. Only a small poertion of the volume has been used.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="aspace_7622128241630fcfda94cea6d0485e2e" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Cases 2019-2862</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1898-1899</unitdate>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_68f0224b3e895409b9a834dc18eaab11">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>The bound volume is a pre-printed case book for diseases of women.  It has spaceas for name, date, age, whether married, number of childreb, number of miscarriages, general appeaernce and conditiion, family history, symptons (broken down by type), menstruation,... diagnosis, and treatment.  There is no publishing information for this pre-printed book. Etheridge enetered an index at the begninning. There is a pasted pice on the cover which syas, Mr. H. L. Humphrey, Masseuse, 4943 Woodlawn Ave."</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
         </c>
         <c id="aspace_0062cc1b054749b19d6c089f8d8f9eb3" level="series">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Powers/Throop family correspondence</unittitle>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_d1a027a2a748d6b9e82edce4da63f103">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>This is correspondence from Harriet (Hattie) Powers Etheridge's side of the family, collected by Hattie Etheridge.  The letters were stored in several boxes odf Amberg's Patent Indexes. Hattie Etheridge was the daughter of Heman G. Powers and Sarah (Throop) Powere. They contain not only letters by and to her, but also letters of mother and father and their relatives, her children, and other relatives.</p>
            </scopecontent>
